---
import ChannelTradeLayout from '../../layouts/ChannelTradeLayout.astro';
import pricing from '../../data/pricing.json';

const benefits = [
  {
    icon: '📱',
    title: 'Receives Drain Fault Photos',
    text: "Homeowners WhatsApp photos of overflowing manholes, lifted inspection chamber covers, and sewage-soaked gardens — 'what do I do?' The AI responds instantly, asks about internal drain performance, and builds a priority emergency lead with the visual evidence."
  },
  {
    icon: '📸',
    title: 'Wins Developer Drainage Slots',
    text: "Main contractors WhatsApp drainage requirements mid-build — 'groundworkers finishing plots 12-16 next week, need foul and surface water drainage following on.' The first drainage firm confirming holds the programme slot."
  },
  {
    icon: '⚡',
    title: 'Captures Solicitor CCTV Bookings',
    text: "Conveyancing solicitors WhatsApp CCTV requests with exchange deadlines — 'need drainage survey on a property in Botley before Friday exchange, buyer insists.' The AI captures the address, the deadline, and the access arrangements."
  },
  {
    icon: '🌙',
    title: 'Active When Drains Block',
    text: "Drains rarely block conveniently. They overflow after heavy rain at midnight, back up on Christmas morning, and flood kitchens during dinner parties. Homeowners WhatsApp drainage engineers in distress. The AI captures every after-hours blocked drain."
  },
  {
    icon: '📋',
    title: 'Structures Quick Drainage Briefs',
    text: "A WhatsApp saying 'drain blocked again, sewage in garden, Kidlington, can you come tomorrow?' becomes a structured emergency lead with recurrence flag, contamination location, access, and urgency timeline."
  },
  {
    icon: '🔒',
    title: 'Professional Business Channel',
    text: "AI WhatsApp runs on your business number. Developer drainage programmes, CCTV survey scheduling, and pipe supplier communications stay separated from personal messaging."
  }
];

const faqs = [
  {
    question: "Can the AI diagnose drain problems from photos?",
    answer: "A drainage defect can only be diagnosed through CCTV survey — a photograph of an overflowing manhole shows the symptom, not the cause. The AI responds constructively: noting the overflow severity, asking whether multiple manholes are affected, whether sewage is entering the property internally, whether the overflow correlates with rainfall, and building a pre-diagnostic lead that prepares you with the correct nozzle type, camera, and excavation assessment before you arrive on site."
  },
  {
    question: "What about multi-message drainage threads?",
    answer: "Drainage conversations develop over multiple messages — a homeowner sends a photo of the overflowing manhole, then explains it happened once before after heavy rain, then confirms the kitchen sink is also backing up, then mentions the large oak tree near the drain run, then asks how much a CCTV survey costs. The AI assembles every fragment into one complete lead with the overflow severity, rainfall correlation, internal backflow, tree proximity, and the survey cost question."
  },
  {
    question: "How much does AI WhatsApp cost for drainage contractors?",
    answer: `WhatsApp is £${pricing.addOn.price}/month as a channel add-on. Emergency jetting generates £150 to £350. A CCTV survey with WRc report generates £250 to £500. A new-build drainage package generates £2,000 to £6,000 per plot. Capturing one solicitor's exchange-deadline CCTV survey — through a rapid WhatsApp response while you operated the jetter on another site — covers the annual channel cost from a single booking.`
  },
  {
    question: "Can I take over a WhatsApp conversation?",
    answer: "Reply once in any thread and the AI relinquishes that conversation permanently. Most drainage engineers let the AI gather the initial brief — blockage location, overflow severity, property type, drainage history, and tree proximity — then engage personally to confirm the attendance time, the equipment required, and the approximate cost."
  },
  {
    question: "How is WhatsApp data from drainage enquiries protected?",
    answer: "Every WhatsApp message — manhole photographs, property addresses, CCTV survey references, Section 104 adoption correspondence, and sender contact details — is encrypted and stored on UK and EU servers under UK GDPR. Your data remains exclusively yours. No drainage project details reach competing firms or third-party aggregators."
  }
];
---

<ChannelTradeLayout
  title="AI WhatsApp for Drainage Contractors | Rapid Receptionist"
  description={`AI WhatsApp for UK drainage contractors. Responds to drain overflow photos, solicitor CCTV requests, and developer programme messages. Add-on at £${pricing.addOn.price}/month.`}
  canonicalUrl="/drainage-contractors/ai-whatsapp/"
  channelName="AI WhatsApp"
  tradeName="Drainage Contractor"
  tradeNamePlural="Drainage Contractors"
  tradeSlug="drainage-contractors"
  headline="AI WhatsApp for Drainage Contractor Companies"
  accentWord="Drainage"
  subhead="A letting agent WhatsApps at 8:15am on a Tuesday with a photo of sewage pooling in the back garden of a rental property in Cowley. The tenant reported the problem at 7am — the ground-floor WC is not flushing, the shower tray is draining slowly, and raw sewage is visible around the cast-iron inspection chamber cover near the boundary wall. The letting agent's message: 'Morning — tenant at 23 Cowley Road reporting sewage in the garden. Photo attached. WC not flushing, shower slow. This is the third time in eighteen months — last two times cleared with jetting but it keeps coming back. The property is a 1950s end-terrace with original clay drains. I suspect the old clay has cracked and roots are getting in from the neighbour's hedge. Need emergency jetting today to clear it for the tenant, then a full CCTV survey to diagnose the root cause. If the pipe needs replacing or lining, we need a quote. Landlord has authority for up to £3,000 without further approval. Can you attend this morning?' You are in a trench on a new-build site in Didcot — connecting a 110mm foul lateral from an inspection chamber to the adopted sewer under a Section 104 agreement, the connection supervised by a Thames Water inspector. Without AI WhatsApp, the Cowley sewage emergency waits until the Thames Water sign-off finishes. With it, the AI responds at 8:16am, confirms your emergency jetting and CCTV capability, and asks whether the tenant can provide access to the rear garden without the letting agent present. She confirms tenant has keys. At noon you dispatch the jetting van: Cowley Road 1950s end-terrace, clay drains, sewage pooling garden, WC not flushing, shower slow, 3rd blockage 18 months, suspected root ingress from neighbour's hedge, jetting + CCTV, landlord £3k authority, tenant access confirmed."
  scenario="It is 10pm on a Saturday in November. A homeowner in Eynsham WhatsApps a video of water bubbling up through his driveway — brown water pushing through a crack in the tarmac near the front of the house. His message: 'Hi — water has started coming up through the driveway. It started about an hour ago during heavy rain. It is brown and smells foul so I think it is sewage not rainwater. The driveway was resurfaced two years ago and the contractor covered over an old manhole — I think they tarmacked over the inspection chamber cover. We have a 1970s detached house. The downstairs WC is still flushing but very slowly. Should I be worried about the foundations? Can someone come Monday to investigate? I think we need the manhole exposed and a CCTV survey. If the pipe has collapsed under the driveway I need to know before it gets worse.' Without AI WhatsApp, the driveway sewage waits until Monday calls. With AI WhatsApp, the reply at 10:01pm: 'Thank you — sewage surfacing through the driveway typically indicates a blockage or collapse downstream of the covered manhole. Could you confirm whether the rear garden has any accessible manholes and whether the property is connected to a shared sewer?' He confirms one rear manhole accessible, shared sewer with the semi next door. Monday you attend: Eynsham 1970s detached, driveway sewage surfacing, tarmacked-over manhole, brown foul water, WC slow, heavy rain, shared sewer, rear manhole accessible, expose manhole + CCTV survey, possible collapse investigation."
  benefits={benefits}
  faqs={faqs}
  channelPageUrl="/construction-trades/ai-whatsapp/"
  tradePageUrl="/drainage-contractors/ai-receptionist/"
  ctaHeadline="Clear the Cowley Sewage Emergency While Thames Water Inspects in Didcot"
  ctaSubhead={`A letting agent with a third blockage in eighteen months, suspected root ingress, and £3k landlord authority needs jetting today and CCTV tomorrow. The AI confirmed while the Section 104 inspector signed off. Add-on at £${pricing.addOn.price}/month.`}
/>
